  <main id="main"><header class="page-hero page-hero--blue-block"><div class="container"><div class="breadcrumbs"><a href="index.html">Home</a> / <a href="society.html">The Society</a> / Convenings & Honors</div><span class="kicker">Gather and recognize</span><h1>Convenings & Honors</h1><p>The Society creates occasions to exchange knowledge, examine major missions, recognize contribution, and strengthen institutional relationships.</p></div></header><nav class="anchor-nav anchor-nav--rail" aria-label="On this page"><div class="container"><a href="#overview"><span>01</span>Overview</a><a href="#focus"><span>02</span>Areas of focus</a><a href="#principles"><span>03</span>Principles</a><a href="#process"><span>04</span>How it works</a><a href="#next"><span>05</span>Next steps</a></div></nav><section class="section profile-opening" id="overview"><div class="container profile-grid"><div class="prose"><span class="eyebrow">Life in the Society</span><h2>Gathering for learning, recognition, and common purpose</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Convenings create focused time for Fellows, hosts, advisors, and partners to examine missions, share practice, and form relationships across fields.</p><p>Honors recognize work of real consequence while keeping attention on the mission, the collaborators, and the responsibilities that accompany distinction.</p><p>Mission forums establishes the point of entry; institutional connection defines what should remain after the immediate work is complete.</p></div><aside class="profile-emblem"><span>Perspective</span><strong>01</strong><p>Mission forums establishes the point of entry; institutional connection defines what should remain after the immediate work is complete.</p></aside></div></section><section class="section" id="focus"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro section-intro--center"><span class="eyebrow">Life in the Society</span><h2>How belonging becomes continued contribution</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Convenings create focused time for Fellows, hosts, advisors, and partners to examine missions, share practice, and form relationships across fields.</p></div><div class="focus-mosaic"><article class="dimension-card"><span>01</span><LegacyIcon name="compass" /><h3>Mission forums</h3><p>Bring evidence, field experience, and different disciplines to a consequential public question.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>02</span><LegacyIcon name="institution" /><h3>Fellow exchanges</h3><p>Create candid spaces to compare methods, challenges, decisions, and lessons from appointments.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>03</span><LegacyIcon name="lightbulb-o" /><h3>Public recognition</h3><p>Elevate contribution that exemplifies excellence, integrity, and meaningful public benefit.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>04</span><LegacyIcon name="handshake-o" /><h3>Institutional connection</h3><p>Help hosts and partners discover shared needs, complementary strengths, and future collaboration.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="section section--mist" id="principles"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">Obligations of membership</span><h2>The practices that sustain a civic society</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Belonging has meaning when recognition is joined to exchange, responsibility, and service.</p></div></div><div class="principle-band-grid"><article class="principle-row"><span>01</span><div><h3>Belonging with purpose</h3><p>Society life creates connection around shared obligations, not status alone.</p></div></article><article class="principle-row"><span>02</span><div><h3>Exchange across fields</h3><p>Fellows learn from people whose disciplines, regions, and experiences differ from their own.</p></div></article><article class="principle-row"><span>03</span><div><h3>A lasting standard</h3><p>The Code of Service continues to guide conduct beyond a single cohort or appointment.</p></div></article></div></section><section class="section section--mist" id="process"><div class="container"><div class="process-header"><div><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">From intent to practice</span><h2>How the Society stays active</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>The Society is sustained through recurring practices that turn affiliation into useful relationships and continued service.</p></div></div><p class="process-pull">Mission forums establishes the point of entry; institutional connection defines what should remain after the immediate work is complete.</p></div><div class="process-milestones"><article class="step"><h3>Welcome</h3><p>Orient Fellows to the standard, one another, and the missions that organize the Society&#x27;s work. Here, attend to mission forums: Bring evidence, field experience, and different disciplines to a consequential public question.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Connect</h3><p>Build trusted peer, advisor, host, and alumni relationships across disciplines and places. Here, attend to fellow exchanges: Create candid spaces to compare methods, challenges, decisions, and lessons from appointments.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Convene</h3><p>Create serious forums for learning, collaboration, reflection, and recognition of contribution. Here, attend to public recognition: Elevate contribution that exemplifies excellence, integrity, and meaningful public benefit.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Continue</h3><p>Carry fellowship forward through mentorship, public-interest work, and future Society missions. Here, attend to institutional connection: Help hosts and partners discover shared needs, complementary strengths, and future collaboration.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="section close-ledger" id="next"><div class="container"><span class="close-ledger__index" aria-hidden="true">05</span><div><div><h2>Continue the work through Society life</h2><p>Begin with mission forums, then define a contribution your capabilities or institution can support.</p></div><div class="actions"><a class="button button--gold" href="apply.html">Participate</a><a class="button button--outline" href="nominate-a-fellow.html">Nominate a Fellow</a></div></div><aside class="related-panel"><span class="eyebrow">Continue exploring</span><h3>Related pathways</h3><ul class="related-list"><li><a href="society.html">The Society</a></li><li><a href="code-of-service.html">Code of Service</a></li><li><a href="convenings-honors.html">Convenings and honors</a></li></ul></aside></div></section></main>

